Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.58,0:05:31.23,Default,Wakana,0000,0000,0000,,Morning, Ren!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.82,0:05:32.93,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Wakana.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.93,0:05:34.99,Default,Wakana,0000,0000,0000,,So how'd it go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.99,0:05:35.87,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,How'd what go?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.87,0:05:39.55,Default,Wakana,0000,0000,0000,,Isn't it obvious? \NYour houseguest from England.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.32,0:05:42.40,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I... don't really know.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.40,0:05:46.30,Default,Wakana,0000,0000,0000,,What the heck? You could \Nat least show me a picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.30,0:05:48.34,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't take one.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.34,0:05:51.66,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,He's sticking around for a while,\N so just come by and see him.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.91,0:05:56.33,Default,Wakana,0000,0000,0000,,That's so hot! Shacking up \Nwith some half-English guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.33,0:05:59.88,Default,Wakana,0000,0000,0000,,What's he in Japan for, anyway?\N Just vacation stuff?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.88,0:06:04.45,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I dunno. Come to think of it, \NI didn't really ask about anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.84,0:06:06.80,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\shad0\blur0.3\fsp5\fnVerdana\fs22\c&H4A443A&\pos(324.667,208)\frz1.471}Ogata Automotive Lt{\fsp1}d.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.51,0:06:12.01,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Is this it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.47,0:06:14.93,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs10\bord1.5\shad0\blur0.3\fay0.012\3c&H5A807F&\c&H56DDDA&\pos(494.667,73.333)}Qualifying Run
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.93,0:06:16.11,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.11,0:06:18.42,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Right on time!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.42,0:06:21.65,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Uh... {\fnTimes New Roman}Are you Kanata Rivington?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.65,0:06:23.97,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,And you're Ogata-san, yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.31,0:06:26.36,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It's a pleasure. I'm Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.83,0:06:29.82,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you actually speak \NJapanese? That's a relief.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.82,0:06:38.66,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8\fnArial\fs26\fsp2\bord0.2\shad1.5\c&H5B452F&\3c&H7F736E&\4c&H6E6E70&\move(-42,62,40,62)}Ogata Automotive
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.24,0:06:34.00,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I hear you went to a \Nfamous English racing school?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.00,0:06:38.23,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I thought Saionji-san was joking\N when he brought it up.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.23,0:06:40.76,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,So I'm sure you're aware,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.76,0:06:45.88,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,but MFG has a bit of a weird rule \Nabout standardized grip-to-weight ratio.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.77,0:06:50.00,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,The strongest cars tend to be \NEuropean models with lots of horsepower
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.00,0:06:52.05,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,and good balance, without a lot of modding.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.82,0:06:56.77,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,As a result, people complain about the rule, \Ncalling it the "rich man's regulation."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.33,0:07:01.97,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Which is why I'm not able to \Nprovide you with a competitive vehicle,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.97,0:07:04.25,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,looking at the big picture \Nof MFG performance.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.25,0:07:05.73,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I've heard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.03,0:07:10.20,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,But I'll be happy just \Ngetting to experience MFG.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.60,0:07:14.66,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! In that case, \NI'll support you in any way I can.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.65,0:07:18.25,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Care to take a look at the car?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.00,0:07:25.42,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.38,0:07:28.92,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.23,0:07:30.48,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,It's so cool.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.48,0:07:34.48,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to flatter me. \NIt's just an old-fashioned three-pedaler.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.48,0:07:35.60,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,Can you work with it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.89,0:07:37.14,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,No problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.60,0:07:41.48,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Back at the academy, H-pattern shifters \Nwith three pedals was the standard.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.70,0:07:43.92,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,I've already taken care of your entry.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.92,0:07:46.67,Default,Ogata,0000,0000,0000,,You're running on the seventh \Nand final day of qualifying.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.94,0:07:49.90,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\bord0\fscx90\an1\shad0\c&H8F9291&\fs16\pos(142,283)\frz346}1st Odahara Pikes Peak Official Qualifying Run
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.94,0:07:49.90,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\an7\fs10\bord1.5\shad0\blur0.3\fay0.012\3c&H2F504D&\c&H56DDDA&\frz345.1\pos(469.333,143.999)}Qualifying Run
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.55,0:07:54.43,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.50,0:07:56.85,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,What a coincidence.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.85,0:07:58.19,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Sure seems like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.66,0:08:00.95,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Are you on your way home \Nfrom school, Ren-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.95,0:08:02.16,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,You can drop the "san."
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.39,0:08:06.13,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,For one thing, I'm younger\N than you. Just "Ren" is fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.14,0:08:09.58,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you coming back from, Kanata?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.58,0:08:13.82,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I went over to Tokyo to visit\Nthe British embassy in Yotsuya.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.25,0:08:16.85,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I also bought a new cell phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.85,0:08:20.81,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Really? In that case, let's swap contact info.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.03,0:08:22.54,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Not, like, in {\i1}that{\i0} way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.54,0:08:26.77,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,But it means, if you need help at all, \Nyou can get in touch with me right away.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.77,0:08:29.81,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Good idea. Hang on a minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.50,0:08:41.75,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,You had work yesterday, \Nright, Ren? What about today?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.75,0:08:45.74,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,My job's a little, uh, irregular.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.74,0:08:49.87,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,It's maybe two or three days a week, \Nthen there's a big gap until the next time.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.87,0:08:50.96,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.96,0:08:54.70,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,I actually wanted to ask \Nyou something, Kanata.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.70,0:08:56.68,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Could we take a picture together?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.68,0:08:58.14,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,A picture?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.14,0:09:01.68,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,When I told my friend about you, \Nshe wanted to see what you look like.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.99,0:09:02.96,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Is it okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.96,0:09:04.64,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Here I go. Smile!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.77,0:09:09.23,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,That turned out great! Wanna see?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.30,0:09:12.48,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Photos aren't my thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.52,0:09:18.47,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,What made you want to leave home\N and come to Japan, Kanata?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.11,0:09:24.66,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I don't mind making an \Nexception and telling you, Ren.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.05,0:09:27.85,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,I came to Japan for two reasons.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.85,0:09:30.73,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,Well, really, it's only one.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.73,0:09:31.92,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.35,0:09:37.19,Default,Kanata,0000,0000,0000,,To find my missing father.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.98,0:09:39.45,Default,Ren,0000,0000,0000,,Your dad?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.93,0:09:42.26,Default,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fax-0.2\bord0\fnImpact\shad0\fs90\b1\c&HFCFFFC&\move(-140,218,200,218)}MF Ghost
